It's understood some stations are battling serious shortages of DNA and rape kits, affecting the turnover time of cases. JOHANNESBURG - Police say there are enough evidence collection kits nationally despite shortages at specific police stations. It's understood some stations are battling serious shortages of DNA and rape kits, affecting the turnover time of cases. Authorities say they’re addressing the issue and will enter into a tender process to procure more kits. The police's Vish Naidoo explained: “We put plans in place to ensure those stations that do have kits in excess can assist those stations that don’t have.” (Edited by Shimoney Regter)